text:
I cannot say anything more than: it works for me, and you are obviously doing
something wrong. Please double check your installation (esp that the temp dir
does exist), and don't reopen the report.

Note: I am uninstalling / reinstalling Tomcat all the time, and never
experienced that issue, so this is not reproduceable, at least not the way you
described it. BTW, I have seen plenty of non Tomcat related file handling
weirdness on XP over the past year ...
creator: remm@apache.org

text:
Hi, I'm just writing to say that I've had the same problem on a linux machine
with tomcat 4 - what was causing this was a dangling symlink in 
/usr/share/tomcat4/common/lib/ (in my case it was the file commons-pool.jar).

So take a look in the analogous directory on your computer, and make sure you
have all the jar files necessary in there

- Yury
creator: ysulsky@hotmail.com
